Vheadline
p2
VA family of artistes
p3
sVnews
p4
VThe Parupalli family is well known for their contribution to music and art. Stalwarts like Balamuralikrishna, Sheik Chinna Moula Sahib and others are reported to have started their initial training from the Parupalli family at Vijayawada before migrating to Chennai.Each member of their family is a singer, an accomplished percussionist or a writer.They now brought out a book titledSundarakandawritten by Parupalli Sreerama Chandra Murthy at Thyagaraja Gana Sabha on November 8. The book, written in Telugu, highlights the scenes of Hanuman&#8217;s quest for tracing Sita. The story was written mainly for the younger generation.The book was released by P. Srinivas, grandson of late M.S. Rama Rao who was famous for his lyrical poetrySundarakanda. Astrologer Srinivas Gargeya, novelist Munipalli Bakka Raju, and Sandeep Gupta and Sreedhar from Royal Media Group also graced the occasion.In connection with the release of book, a music concert was presented by the family members and students. The programme started with Hanumath Geetham by Sailaja, Supriya and Alekhya, students of Sarada Sangeeta Vidyalayam, Vishakapatnam. They began with Charukesi ragaSaranu Kapeeswara, followed byOkkade ekanga Veeruduin Thodi, and concluded withMangambudhi Hanumanthain Dharmavathi. The students were well-trained and confident, rendering the songs flawlessly.The family then presented a Sangeetha rupakam &#8216;Pibare Ramarasam&#8217;. The songs were rendered by all the family members, which included Parupalli Ranganath, who is well known for his famous songSree Venkatesam Sirasanamami, which reverberates all over Tirumala. Supporting him were Parupalli Satyanarayana, Parupalli Sriram Charan and Pridhvi Chandra. The narration was given by Parupalli Sree Rama Chandra Murthy, who also sang along.The singers were accompanied by Chakarapani on the violin, who showed his innate talent, as well as Parupalli Subbraya Phalgun and Parupalli Balasubramanyam on the mrindagam. The brothers showed excellent coordination and sense of rhythm. Kamaraju Kishore accompanied on the ghatam. The family proved once again their dedication towards music and it was a treat for the listeners.
